text.tspan: Number of households and children in temporary accommodation in
The total number of households, households with children, and children in England who are in temporary accommodation at
any given point in time. Temporary accommodation is allocated to households with no permanent form of residence or who
face immediate eviction. These figures are included in UK Government statistics on the prevalence of homelessness.
Data source: UK Government (2018). Ministry of Housing, Communities & Local Government
